        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 20 at 7:58PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 758 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Rural Retreat, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Wytheville...
Marion...
Saltville...
Chilhowie...
Rural Retreat...
Mount Rogers National Recreation Area...
and Speedwell.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
